Prime Minister Zaev says joining NATO would bring much-needed investment to Macedonia, whose unemployment rate is more than 20%.
"I think the vast majority will be in favour, as more than 80% of citizens are in favour of the EU and NATO," Zaev said after depositing his vote.
He said a positive outcome would be a "confirmation of our future."
